rComments: Start the assignment as early as possible. It may seem easy at first but it takes a while to find information you need. Other than that the course is very interesting and tests are easy (past tests is a must). Youll be fine, she is the sweetest prof ever!:)

Never had a better prof in my life. She is excited, engaging, passionate, and delivers complex content in an accessible way. She is very helpful in her emails, and her tutorials help to guide your thought process when solving pharmalogical problems.

SARA DA SILVA IS DEFINITELY IN THE TOP 10 BEST PROF AT UTM. She is so passionate about pharmacology and she's VERY interactive in the lectures and tutorials. She's excellent at explaining and notes are well-detailed. Don't need the textbook. Go to everylecture and tutorial and you'll do well. She more than adequately prepares you for the test/exam!

She was an amazing professor, and presented the content of the course very effectively. I didn't really use the textbook much, and used it as reference as she suggested. Her powerpoint is a bible, so make good use of it for your study and you'll do good. She's super caring and helpful, so it'll will be for your best to clarify unclear points.

A really good prof she takes what could be seen as a dull course and tries to make it as interesting as possible. Lectures are really worth going to and she encourages in lecture participation. Fast responses to emails and easy to reach outside of class. The course is memorization heavy but if you go to the lectures and tutorials you should be fine
